title: 2020 Alaska House of Representatives election
deleted: Four races have not been called by independent media outlets and the outcomes could change once all votes are counted or recounts take place.
#District 15: Republican David Nelson leads Democrat Lyn Franks by 91 votes (or 1.8%) in this Republican-held open seat.
#District 25: Democrat Liz Snyder leads incumbent Republican (and House Minority Leader) Lance Pruitt by 17 votes (or 0.2%).

#District 26: Republican James Kaufman leads Democratic-backed Independent Suzanne LaFrance by 453 votes (or 3.7%) in this Republican-held open seat. Fully Independent candidate Benjamin Fletcher currently has 493 votes, more than the margin between the two candidates.
#District 40: Independent Josiah "Aullaqsruaq" Patkotak leads Democrat Elizabeth Ferguson by 148 votes (or 3.8%) in this Democratic-held open seat.
